{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780928806055,"sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_zS25j1ftHVYRtgo35GLT9ebx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","offset":118,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n118:   hooks, and graph server within one process. WAL mode permits concurrent readers\n119:   with a single writer; cross-process safety relies on SQLite's file locking.\n120: - `registry.json` is a small JSON map. Concurrent writes are rare (only during\n121:   `/openltm:project register` or `SessionStart` first-touch) but unsynchronised — a\n122:   known weakness called out in §7.\n123: - `context-summary.md` is a write-mostly artifact regenerated by `PreCompact`. It is\n124:   never the source of truth; the DB is.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. Component Diagram (C4 Level 3)\n129: \n130: This level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\n131: components. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\n132: have no internal components.\n133: \n134: ### 3.1 MCP Server components\n135: \n136: ```mermaid\n137: C4Component\n138:   title MCP Server — Components\n139: \n140:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n141:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n142: \n143:   Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n144:     Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n145:     Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n146:     Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n147:     Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n148:     Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n149:     Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n150:     Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n151:     Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n152:   }\n153: \n154:   Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n155:   Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n156:   Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n157:   Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n158:   Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n159:   Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n160:   Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n161:   Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n162:   Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n163:   Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n164:   Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n165:   Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n169: \n170: ```mermaid\n171: C4Component\n172:   title Hook Runners — Components\n173: \n174:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n175:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n176:   ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n177:   ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n178: \n179:   Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n180:     Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n181:     Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n182:     Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n183:     Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n184:     Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n185:     Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n186:     Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n187:   }\n188: \n189:   Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n190:   Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n191:   Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n192:   Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n193:   Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n194:   Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n195:   Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n196:   Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n197:   Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n198:   Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n199:   Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n200:   Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n201:   Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **Component responsibilities at a glance**\n205: \n206: | Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n207: |-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n208: | Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n209: | Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n210: | Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n211: | Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n212: | Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n213: | Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n214: | Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n219: \n220: This is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\n221: A \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\n222: compaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n223: \n224: ```mermaid\n225: sequenceDiagram\n226:   autonumber\n227:   actor Dev as Developer\n\n(Showing lines 118-227 of 1075. Use offset=228 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  hooks, and graph server within one process. WAL mode permits concurrent readers\n  with a single writer; cross-process safety relies on SQLite's file locking.\n- `registry.json` is a small JSON map. Concurrent writes are rare (only during\n  `/openltm:project register` or `SessionStart` first-touch) but unsynchronised — a\n  known weakness called out in §7.\n- `context-summary.md` is a write-mostly artifact regenerated by `PreCompact`. It is\n  never the source of truth; the DB is.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Component Diagram (C4 Level 3)\n\nThis level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\ncomponents. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\nhave no internal components.\n\n### 3.1 MCP Server components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","text":"  hooks, and graph server within one process. WAL mode permits concurrent readers\n  with a single writer; cross-process safety relies on SQLite's file locking.\n- `registry.json` is a small JSON map. Concurrent writes are rare (only during\n  `/openltm:project register` or `SessionStart` first-touch) but unsynchronised — a\n  known weakness called out in §7.\n- `context-summary.md` is a write-mostly artifact regenerated by `PreCompact`. It is\n  never the source of truth; the DB is.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Component Diagram (C4 Level 3)\n\nThis level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\ncomponents. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\nhave no internal components.\n\n### 3.1 MCP Server components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title MCP Server — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n    Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n    Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n    Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n    Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n    Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n    Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n    Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n    Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n  Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n  Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n  Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n  Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n  Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n  Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n  Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n  Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n  Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n  Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n  Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n```\n\n### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title Hook Runners — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n  ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n  ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n    Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n    Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n    Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n    Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n    Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n    Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n    Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n  Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n  Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n  Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n  Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n  Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n  Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n  Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n  Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n  Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n  Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n  Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n  Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n```\n\n**Component responsibilities at a glance**\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n|-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n| Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n| Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n| Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n| Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n| Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n| Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n\nThis is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\nA \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\ncompaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n  autonumber\n  actor Dev as Developer","lineStart":118,"lineEnd":227,"totalLines":1075,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","time":{"start":1780928806043,"end":1780928806053}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06533a27e20374c3016a26d125ff3c819183c0854ad29e05f2"}},"id":"prt_ea7a0fc93001GygWAOE5MTYW68","sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","messageID":"msg_ea7a0bde9001hGl1O24KkYMeLf"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780928806120,"sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_NJdH2wgYCo3aP1ZKowunWnyi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","offset":229,"limit":95},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n229:   participant Start as SessionStart hook\n230:   participant Reg as registry.json\n231:   participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n232:   participant MCP as MCP Server\n233:   participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n234:   participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n235:   participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n236:   participant Sum as context-summary.md\n237: \n238:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n239:   Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n240:   Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n241:   Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n242:   Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n243:   Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n244:   Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n245: \n246:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n247:   Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n248:   Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n249:   MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n250:   alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n251:     MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n252:     MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n253:   end\n254:   MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n255:   MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n256:   Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n257: \n258:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n259:   Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n260:   Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n261:   MCP->>MCP: redact secrets; compute dedup_key\n262:   MCP->>DB: INSERT memories (trigger writes memories_fts)\n263:   MCP-->>Claude: { id }\n264: \n265:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Mid-session: compaction ---\n266:   Claude->>Pre: spawn(PreCompact)\n267:   Pre->>DB: SELECT all 4 context types for project\n268:   Pre->>Sum: write context-summary.md (~60 lines, fallback)\n269:   Pre-->>Claude: ack\n270:   Claude->>Claude: compact transcript\n271:   Note over Claude: Next assistant turn re-reads context-summary.md if needed\n272: \n273:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session end ---\n274:   Claude->>Update: spawn(UpdateContext)\n275:   Update->>DB: INSERT progress; trim oldest > 20; UPDATE last_touched\n276:   Update-->>Claude: ack\n277:   Claude->>Eval: spawn(EvaluateSession)\n278:   Eval->>DB: scan transcript-derived signals; propose / write candidate insights\n279:   Eval-->>Claude: ack\n280:   Claude-->>Dev: clean exit\n281: ```\n282: \n283: **Per-step contracts**\n284: \n285: | Step | Read from | Writes to | Failure mode |\n286: |------|-----------|-----------|--------------|\n287: | SessionStart | DB, registry | registry (auto-register only) | Hook silent-fail → no injection; `/openltm:doctor` detects |\n288: | recall | DB (FTS5 + base) | DB (last_recalled_at, recall_count) | Returns empty array; never throws into Claude |\n289: | learn | — | DB (memories, memories_fts via trigger) | Reject duplicate dedup_key; redact before write |\n290: | PreCompact | DB | context-summary.md | If write fails, post-compact session loses fallback only |\n291: | EvaluateSession | transcript signals, DB | DB (memories) | OQ4 — propose vs. auto-write is open |\n292: | UpdateContext | — | DB (context_items progress) | Trim ensures bounded growth |\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## 5. Data Model Overview\n297: \n298: The persistent store is one SQLite file (`openltm.db`) under `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}`.\n299: Schema lives in `src/schema.sql` and is extended idempotently by migrations in\n300: `src/shared-db.ts`. WAL mode is enabled for read-during-write concurrency.\n301: \n302: ### 5.1 Tables\n303: \n304: | Table | Purpose | Lifecycle |\n305: |-------|---------|-----------|\n306: | `memories` | Long-term, durable insights (decisions, gotchas, patterns, etc.). Global or project-scoped. | Permanent unless soft-deleted via `status` |\n307: | `context_items` | Short-term, per-project context. The 4 PRD-defined types: goal, decision, progress, gotcha. | Mixed: progress trimmed to last 20; goal replaced; decision/gotcha permanent |\n308: | `tags` | Tag dictionary (unique names). | Auto-created on use |\n309: | `memory_tags` | M:N join — memory ↔ tag. | Cascading on memory delete |\n310: | `memory_relations` | Knowledge graph edges between memories with typed relationship. | Cascading on memory delete |\n311: | `memories_fts` | FTS5 virtual table mirroring `memories.content`. | Maintained by triggers (insert/update/delete) |\n312: | `settings` | Key-value config for janitor / provider settings. | Manual or migration-managed |\n313: \n314: ### 5.2 `memories` — key columns\n315: \n316: | Column | Purpose |\n317: |--------|---------|\n318: | `id` | Primary key, surrogate `INTEGER` |\n319: | `content` | The memory text. Subject to redaction on write. |\n320: | `category` | One of: `preference`, `architecture`, `gotcha`, `pattern`, `workflow`, `constraint` |\n321: | `importance` | 1–5; `5` opts a global memory into every-session injection |\n322: | `confidence` | 0.0–1.0; reserved for janitor / promotion logic |\n323: | `project_scope` | NULL = global; else project_name (joined with registry) |\n\n(Showing lines 229-323 of 1075. Use offset=324 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  participant Start as SessionStart hook\n  participant Reg as registry.json\n  participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n  participant MCP as MCP Server\n  participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n  participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n  participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n  participant Sum as context-summary.md\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n  Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n  Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n  Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n  Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n  Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n  Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n  Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n  Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","text":"  participant Start as SessionStart hook\n  participant Reg as registry.json\n  participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n  participant MCP as MCP Server\n  participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n  participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n  participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n  participant Sum as context-summary.md\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n  Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n  Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n  Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n  Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n  Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n  Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n  Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n  Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n  MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n  alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n    MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n    MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n  end\n  MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n  MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n  Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n  Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n  Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n  MCP->>MCP: redact secrets; compute dedup_key\n  MCP->>DB: INSERT memories (trigger writes memories_fts)\n  MCP-->>Claude: { id }\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Mid-session: compaction ---\n  Claude->>Pre: spawn(PreCompact)\n  Pre->>DB: SELECT all 4 context types for project\n  Pre->>Sum: write context-summary.md (~60 lines, fallback)\n  Pre-->>Claude: ack\n  Claude->>Claude: compact transcript\n  Note over Claude: Next assistant turn re-reads context-summary.md if needed\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session end ---\n  Claude->>Update: spawn(UpdateContext)\n  Update->>DB: INSERT progress; trim oldest > 20; UPDATE last_touched\n  Update-->>Claude: ack\n  Claude->>Eval: spawn(EvaluateSession)\n  Eval->>DB: scan transcript-derived signals; propose / write candidate insights\n  Eval-->>Claude: ack\n  Claude-->>Dev: clean exit\n```\n\n**Per-step contracts**\n\n| Step | Read from | Writes to | Failure mode |\n|------|-----------|-----------|--------------|\n| SessionStart | DB, registry | registry (auto-register only) | Hook silent-fail → no injection; `/openltm:doctor` detects |\n| recall | DB (FTS5 + base) | DB (last_recalled_at, recall_count) | Returns empty array; never throws into Claude |\n| learn | — | DB (memories, memories_fts via trigger) | Reject duplicate dedup_key; redact before write |\n| PreCompact | DB | context-summary.md | If write fails, post-compact session loses fallback only |\n| EvaluateSession | transcript signals, DB | DB (memories) | OQ4 — propose vs. auto-write is open |\n| UpdateContext | — | DB (context_items progress) | Trim ensures bounded growth |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Data Model Overview\n\nThe persistent store is one SQLite file (`openltm.db`) under `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}`.\nSchema lives in `src/schema.sql` and is extended idempotently by migrations in\n`src/shared-db.ts`. WAL mode is enabled for read-during-write concurrency.\n\n### 5.1 Tables\n\n| Table | Purpose | Lifecycle |\n|-------|---------|-----------|\n| `memories` | Long-term, durable insights (decisions, gotchas, patterns, etc.). Global or project-scoped. | Permanent unless soft-deleted via `status` |\n| `context_items` | Short-term, per-project context. The 4 PRD-defined types: goal, decision, progress, gotcha. | Mixed: progress trimmed to last 20; goal replaced; decision/gotcha permanent |\n| `tags` | Tag dictionary (unique names). | Auto-created on use |\n| `memory_tags` | M:N join — memory ↔ tag. | Cascading on memory delete |\n| `memory_relations` | Knowledge graph edges between memories with typed relationship. | Cascading on memory delete |\n| `memories_fts` | FTS5 virtual table mirroring `memories.content`. | Maintained by triggers (insert/update/delete) |\n| `settings` | Key-value config for janitor / provider settings. | Manual or migration-managed |\n\n### 5.2 `memories` — key columns\n\n| Column | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `id` | Primary key, surrogate `INTEGER` |\n| `content` | The memory text. Subject to redaction on write. |\n| `category` | One of: `preference`, `architecture`, `gotcha`, `pattern`, `workflow`, `constraint` |\n| `importance` | 1–5; `5` opts a global memory into every-session injection |\n| `confidence` | 0.0–1.0; reserved for janitor / promotion logic |\n| `project_scope` | NULL = global; else project_name (joined with registry) |","lineStart":229,"lineEnd":323,"totalLines":1075,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","time":{"start":1780928806091,"end":1780928806115}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06533a27e20374c3016a26d125ff688191ad0cd6c7b83d1f48"}},"id":"prt_ea7a0fcbf001V0Yuug0ukXohts","sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","messageID":"msg_ea7a0bde9001hGl1O24KkYMeLf"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780928806126,"sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3XwQWqwtxNH1qpOLBTgRTpaT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","offset":331,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n331: ### 5.3 `context_items` — key columns\n332: \n333: | Column | Purpose |\n334: |--------|---------|\n335: | `project_name` | Foreign-keyed by name to the registry |\n336: | `type` | `goal` / `decision` / `progress` / `gotcha` |\n337: | `content` | Free text |\n338: | `permanent` | 1 for decision/gotcha; 0 for goal/progress |\n339: | `memory_id` | Optional link back to a promoted global memory |\n340: | `status` | `active` / `pending_promotion` / `promoted` |\n341: \n342: ### 5.4 FTS5 setup\n343: \n344: - `memories_fts` is a `content='memories'` external-content FTS5 virtual table.\n345:   Triggers (`memories_ai`, `memories_au`, `memories_ad`) keep the index in sync on\n346:   insert/update/delete.\n347: - Recall path: parameterised `MATCH` query against `memories_fts`, joined back to\n348:   `memories` for category/project/importance filters and decay scoring.\n349: - BM25 ranking is the default; the recall engine post-multiplies by importance and\n350:   decay factors before returning top-N.\n351: \n352: ### 5.5 Decay model (current)\n353: \n354: The current implementation applies decay at recall time, not as a stored score.\n355: \n356: - **Inputs:** `last_recalled_at`, `recall_count`, `importance`, `created_at`.\n357: - **Rule sketch:**\n358:   - If `importance == 5`, no decay.\n359:   - If memory has not been recalled in 90+ days and `importance < 3`, multiply rank\n360:     by a decay factor (< 1).\n361:   - Recently-recalled memories get a freshness boost.\n362: - **Reporting:** `/openltm:health` summarises memories by decay bucket\n363:   (`fresh` / `aging` / `stale`) and surfaces top-5 staleness candidates.\n364: - **OQ3** (PRD §9): the exact function (linear / exponential / recall-driven) is open\n365:   and intended to be tuned with real recall logs.\n366: \n367: ### 5.6 Relationships\n368: \n369: ```mermaid\n370: erDiagram\n371:   memories ||--o{ memory_tags : tagged\n372:   tags ||--o{ memory_tags : labels\n373:   memories ||--o{ memory_relations : \"source/target\"\n374:   memories ||--o| memories : superseded_by\n375:   memories ||--o{ context_items : promoted_from\n376:   memories ||--|| memories_fts : \"FTS5 mirror\"\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### 5.7 Registry (out-of-DB)\n380: \n381: `~/.claude/projects/registry.json` holds the cwd → project_name map. It is a JSON\n382: file (not a table) for cross-plugin readability and trivial inspection. Concurrent\n383: write safety is **not** guaranteed — a known weakness (§7).\n384: \n385: ---\n386: \n387: ## 6. Architectural Decision Records\n388: \n389: Each ADR is short and load-bearing. Format: Status, Context, Decision, Alternatives,\n390: Consequences. Every ADR includes at least one rejected alternative.\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### ADR-001 — SQLite as the storage engine\n395: \n396: **Status:** Accepted. In production since v1.0.\n397: \n398: **Context.** The plugin needs durable, queryable, low-latency storage on the\n399: developer's machine. It must survive Claude Code restarts, plugin upgrades, and\n400: machine sleep. Median write latency target: < 50 ms p95 (PRD §8.4 R3). Median recall\n401: < 200 ms (G2). Zero cloud dependency by default (PRD §7 N1).\n402: \n403: **Decision.** Use SQLite (via `bun:sqlite`) in WAL mode, single file at\n404: `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/openltm.db`. FTS5 virtual table for full-text search.\n405: \n406: **Alternatives considered.**\n407: \n408: - **Postgres / managed DB.** Rejected. Adds an installation dependency, defeats the\n409:   zero-cloud promise, and is overkill for single-user data volumes (~10⁴–10⁶ rows\n410:   realistic ceiling).\n411: - **Flat JSON / Markdown files (the pre-1.0 design).** Rejected. No transactional\n412:   semantics, no FTS, no concurrent reader safety, O(N) scan per recall. The current\n413:   `context-summary.md` is the vestigial fallback; it is a *projection*, not the truth.\n414: - **DuckDB.** Considered. Better analytical perf, but heavier binary, weaker FTS\n415:   story, less Bun-native tooling, and write-heavy workloads (learn + decay updates)\n416:   favour SQLite.\n417: - **LevelDB / RocksDB key-value.** Rejected. No SQL, no FTS5, would need a hand-rolled\n418:   index for every query path.\n419: \n420: **Consequences.**\n\n(Showing lines 331-420 of 1075. Use offset=421 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### 5.3 `context_items` — key columns\n\n| Column | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `project_name` | Foreign-keyed by name to the registry |\n| `type` | `goal` / `decision` / `progress` / `gotcha` |\n| `content` | Free text |\n| `permanent` | 1 for decision/gotcha; 0 for goal/progress |\n| `memory_id` | Optional link back to a promoted global memory |\n| `status` | `active` / `pending_promotion` / `promoted` |\n\n### 5.4 FTS5 setup\n\n- `memories_fts` is a `content='memories'` external-content FTS5 virtual table.\n  Triggers (`memories_ai`, `memories_au`, `memories_ad`) keep the index in sync on\n  insert/update/delete.\n- Recall path: parameterised `MATCH` query against `memories_fts`, joined back to\n  `memories` for category/project/importance filters and decay scoring.\n- BM25 ranking is the default; the recall engine post-multiplies by importance and\n  decay factors before returning top-N.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","text":"### 5.3 `context_items` — key columns\n\n| Column | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `project_name` | Foreign-keyed by name to the registry |\n| `type` | `goal` / `decision` / `progress` / `gotcha` |\n| `content` | Free text |\n| `permanent` | 1 for decision/gotcha; 0 for goal/progress |\n| `memory_id` | Optional link back to a promoted global memory |\n| `status` | `active` / `pending_promotion` / `promoted` |\n\n### 5.4 FTS5 setup\n\n- `memories_fts` is a `content='memories'` external-content FTS5 virtual table.\n  Triggers (`memories_ai`, `memories_au`, `memories_ad`) keep the index in sync on\n  insert/update/delete.\n- Recall path: parameterised `MATCH` query against `memories_fts`, joined back to\n  `memories` for category/project/importance filters and decay scoring.\n- BM25 ranking is the default; the recall engine post-multiplies by importance and\n  decay factors before returning top-N.\n\n### 5.5 Decay model (current)\n\nThe current implementation applies decay at recall time, not as a stored score.\n\n- **Inputs:** `last_recalled_at`, `recall_count`, `importance`, `created_at`.\n- **Rule sketch:**\n  - If `importance == 5`, no decay.\n  - If memory has not been recalled in 90+ days and `importance < 3`, multiply rank\n    by a decay factor (< 1).\n  - Recently-recalled memories get a freshness boost.\n- **Reporting:** `/openltm:health` summarises memories by decay bucket\n  (`fresh` / `aging` / `stale`) and surfaces top-5 staleness candidates.\n- **OQ3** (PRD §9): the exact function (linear / exponential / recall-driven) is open\n  and intended to be tuned with real recall logs.\n\n### 5.6 Relationships\n\n```mermaid\nerDiagram\n  memories ||--o{ memory_tags : tagged\n  tags ||--o{ memory_tags : labels\n  memories ||--o{ memory_relations : \"source/target\"\n  memories ||--o| memories : superseded_by\n  memories ||--o{ context_items : promoted_from\n  memories ||--|| memories_fts : \"FTS5 mirror\"\n```\n\n### 5.7 Registry (out-of-DB)\n\n`~/.claude/projects/registry.json` holds the cwd → project_name map. It is a JSON\nfile (not a table) for cross-plugin readability and trivial inspection. Concurrent\nwrite safety is **not** guaranteed — a known weakness (§7).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Architectural Decision Records\n\nEach ADR is short and load-bearing. Format: Status, Context, Decision, Alternatives,\nConsequences. Every ADR includes at least one rejected alternative.\n\n---\n\n### ADR-001 — SQLite as the storage engine\n\n**Status:** Accepted. In production since v1.0.\n\n**Context.** The plugin needs durable, queryable, low-latency storage on the\ndeveloper's machine. It must survive Claude Code restarts, plugin upgrades, and\nmachine sleep. Median write latency target: < 50 ms p95 (PRD §8.4 R3). Median recall\n< 200 ms (G2). Zero cloud dependency by default (PRD §7 N1).\n\n**Decision.** Use SQLite (via `bun:sqlite`) in WAL mode, single file at\n`${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/openltm.db`. FTS5 virtual table for full-text search.\n\n**Alternatives considered.**\n\n- **Postgres / managed DB.** Rejected. Adds an installation dependency, defeats the\n  zero-cloud promise, and is overkill for single-user data volumes (~10⁴–10⁶ rows\n  realistic ceiling).\n- **Flat JSON / Markdown files (the pre-1.0 design).** Rejected. No transactional\n  semantics, no FTS, no concurrent reader safety, O(N) scan per recall. The current\n  `context-summary.md` is the vestigial fallback; it is a *projection*, not the truth.\n- **DuckDB.** Considered. Better analytical perf, but heavier binary, weaker FTS\n  story, less Bun-native tooling, and write-heavy workloads (learn + decay updates)\n  favour SQLite.\n- **LevelDB / RocksDB key-value.** Rejected. No SQL, no FTS5, would need a hand-rolled\n  index for every query path.\n\n**Consequences.**","lineStart":331,"lineEnd":420,"totalLines":1075,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","time":{"start":1780928806100,"end":1780928806124}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06533a27e20374c3016a26d125ff74819193366f8267acb7d3"}},"id":"prt_ea7a0fccf001XUqEuSm9HvYOLi","sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","messageID":"msg_ea7a0bde9001hGl1O24KkYMeLf"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780928806137,"sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oWcXgth8PX7karCoKCQanXci","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","offset":145,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n145: \n146: | Hook | Trigger | Job |\n147: |------|---------|-----|\n148: | `SessionStart` | Claude Code session opens | Resolve project from registry, regenerate `context-summary.md`, inject up to ~60 lines of context, inject importance-5 globals + top-15 project memories. |\n149: | `PreCompact` | Before context compaction | Read DB for all 4 context types, write `context-summary.md` (~60 lines max) so post-compact session restores cleanly. |\n150: | `EvaluateSession` | Session end / interval | Score the session; promote candidate insights for learning. |\n151: | `UpdateContext` | Session end | Append progress entries (trimmed to last 20), update last-touched timestamps. |\n152: \n153: ### 4.4 Skills (`./skills/`)\n154: \n155: | Skill | When |\n156: |-------|------|\n157: | `ContinuousLearning` | Reference for LTM memory commands, context hooks, DB schema. Loaded when user mentions learn/recall/forget/relate or session boundaries. |\n158: | `Learned` | Reference for retrieved patterns and lessons from past sessions. |\n159: | `session-context` | Session context persistence playbook (goals, decisions, progress, gotchas). |\n160: | `GitLearn` | Retroactive Git commit learning — backfill memories from history. Trigger: \"git learn\", \"review past commits\", \"backfill learnings\". |\n161: \n162: ### 4.5 Storage & Registry\n163: \n164: - **Database:** SQLite at `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/openltm.db` (resolved by Claude Code).\n165: - **Schema:** `src/schema.sql`. Two main tables: `memories` (long-term, permanent) and\n166:   `context_items` (short-term, project-scoped, auto-trimmed).\n167: - **Registry:** `~/.claude/projects/registry.json` — maps cwd → project name. Auto-populated by `SessionStart`.\n168: - **Cache mirror:** `~/.claude/plugins/cache/ltm/ltm/<version>/` — the plugin loader reads\n169:   from cache, so hot-patch flow requires patching cache or bumping version.\n170: \n171: ### 4.6 Auxiliary Servers\n172: \n173: - **MCP server** (`src/mcp-server.ts`) — primary tool surface, started by Claude Code per `mcpServers` in `plugin.json`.\n174: - **Graph visualization server** (`src/graph-server.ts`) — opt-in localhost web UI for\n175:   exploring memory graphs. Managed via `/openltm:admin server`.\n176: - **Graph app** (`graph-app/`) — front-end for the visualization, has its own Playwright\n177:   E2E test harness (`bun run test:e2e`).\n178: \n179: ### 4.7 Memory Categories\n180: `preference` · `architecture` · `gotcha` · `pattern` · `workflow` · `constraint`\n181: plus the **importance** scalar (1-5) used to gate global injection.\n182: \n183: ### 4.8 Context Item Types (project-scoped, short-term)\n184: `goal` (1-3 lines, current objective) · `decision` (permanent) · `progress` (rolling, last 20) · `gotcha` (permanent).\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 5. User Stories with Acceptance Criteria\n189: \n190: All ACs use Given/When/Then form. They are tight enough for **qa-tester** to automate\n191: and for **system-architect** to design against.\n192: \n193: ### US-1 — Auto-restore project context at session start\n194: **As** Sam, **I want** my project's goal, recent decisions, and gotchas restored when I open a session, **so that** I don't have to re-explain.\n195: \n196: **Acceptance criteria:**\n197: - **Given** a registered project with at least one `goal` and one `decision` in the DB,\n198:   **when** Claude Code session starts in that project's cwd,\n199:   **then** a `## Restored Project Context` block appears in the session, containing the goal, up to N decisions, up to N gotchas, and last 5 progress entries.\n200: - **Given** the same project, **when** session starts, **then** importance-5 global memories are also injected.\n201: - **Given** total restored context exceeds 60 lines, **when** injected, **then** it is truncated to ~60 lines with a \"+N more — run /openltm:memory recall\" footer.\n202: \n203: ### US-2 — Recall before deciding\n204: **As** Pat, **I want** `recall` to surface prior decisions on a topic, **so that** I don't contradict past work.\n205: \n206: **Acceptance criteria:**\n207: - **Given** a memory exists with text \"we use Bun, not npm\", **when** I call `recall(\"javascript package manager\")`, **then** that memory ranks in the top 3 results.\n208: - **Given** the same DB, **when** the FTS5 query returns < 3 results, **then** semantic fallback runs and merges results, deduplicated by id.\n209: - **Given** I pass `category: \"gotcha\"`, **when** I recall, **then** only gotchas are returned.\n210: - **Given** a project filter, **when** I recall, **then** only memories tagged with that project (or no project) are returned.\n211: \n212: ### US-3 — Learn a decision in 1 keystroke\n213: **As** Sam, **I want** to capture a decision without leaving flow, **so that** I actually do it.\n214: \n\n(Showing lines 145-214 of 496. Use offset=215 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n| Hook | Trigger | Job |\n|------|---------|-----|\n| `SessionStart` | Claude Code session opens | Resolve project from registry, regenerate `context-summary.md`, inject up to ~60 lines of context, inject importance-5 globals + top-15 project memories. |\n| `PreCompact` | Before context compaction | Read DB for all 4 context types, write `context-summary.md` (~60 lines max) so post-compact session restores cleanly. |\n| `EvaluateSession` | Session end / interval | Score the session; promote candidate insights for learning. |\n| `UpdateContext` | Session end | Append progress entries (trimmed to last 20), update last-touched timestamps. |\n\n### 4.4 Skills (`./skills/`)\n\n| Skill | When |\n|-------|------|\n| `ContinuousLearning` | Reference for LTM memory commands, context hooks, DB schema. Loaded when user mentions learn/recall/forget/relate or session boundaries. |\n| `Learned` | Reference for retrieved patterns and lessons from past sessions. |\n| `session-context` | Session context persistence playbook (goals, decisions, progress, gotchas). |\n| `GitLearn` | Retroactive Git commit learning — backfill memories from history. Trigger: \"git learn\", \"review past commits\", \"backfill learnings\". |\n\n### 4.5 Storage & Registry\n\n- **Database:** SQLite at `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/openltm.db` (resolved by Claude Code).","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","text":"\n| Hook | Trigger | Job |\n|------|---------|-----|\n| `SessionStart` | Claude Code session opens | Resolve project from registry, regenerate `context-summary.md`, inject up to ~60 lines of context, inject importance-5 globals + top-15 project memories. |\n| `PreCompact` | Before context compaction | Read DB for all 4 context types, write `context-summary.md` (~60 lines max) so post-compact session restores cleanly. |\n| `EvaluateSession` | Session end / interval | Score the session; promote candidate insights for learning. |\n| `UpdateContext` | Session end | Append progress entries (trimmed to last 20), update last-touched timestamps. |\n\n### 4.4 Skills (`./skills/`)\n\n| Skill | When |\n|-------|------|\n| `ContinuousLearning` | Reference for LTM memory commands, context hooks, DB schema. Loaded when user mentions learn/recall/forget/relate or session boundaries. |\n| `Learned` | Reference for retrieved patterns and lessons from past sessions. |\n| `session-context` | Session context persistence playbook (goals, decisions, progress, gotchas). |\n| `GitLearn` | Retroactive Git commit learning — backfill memories from history. Trigger: \"git learn\", \"review past commits\", \"backfill learnings\". |\n\n### 4.5 Storage & Registry\n\n- **Database:** SQLite at `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/openltm.db` (resolved by Claude Code).\n- **Schema:** `src/schema.sql`. Two main tables: `memories` (long-term, permanent) and\n  `context_items` (short-term, project-scoped, auto-trimmed).\n- **Registry:** `~/.claude/projects/registry.json` — maps cwd → project name. Auto-populated by `SessionStart`.\n- **Cache mirror:** `~/.claude/plugins/cache/ltm/ltm/<version>/` — the plugin loader reads\n  from cache, so hot-patch flow requires patching cache or bumping version.\n\n### 4.6 Auxiliary Servers\n\n- **MCP server** (`src/mcp-server.ts`) — primary tool surface, started by Claude Code per `mcpServers` in `plugin.json`.\n- **Graph visualization server** (`src/graph-server.ts`) — opt-in localhost web UI for\n  exploring memory graphs. Managed via `/openltm:admin server`.\n- **Graph app** (`graph-app/`) — front-end for the visualization, has its own Playwright\n  E2E test harness (`bun run test:e2e`).\n\n### 4.7 Memory Categories\n`preference` · `architecture` · `gotcha` · `pattern` · `workflow` · `constraint`\nplus the **importance** scalar (1-5) used to gate global injection.\n\n### 4.8 Context Item Types (project-scoped, short-term)\n`goal` (1-3 lines, current objective) · `decision` (permanent) · `progress` (rolling, last 20) · `gotcha` (permanent).\n\n---\n\n## 5. User Stories with Acceptance Criteria\n\nAll ACs use Given/When/Then form. They are tight enough for **qa-tester** to automate\nand for **system-architect** to design against.\n\n### US-1 — Auto-restore project context at session start\n**As** Sam, **I want** my project's goal, recent decisions, and gotchas restored when I open a session, **so that** I don't have to re-explain.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- **Given** a registered project with at least one `goal` and one `decision` in the DB,\n  **when** Claude Code session starts in that project's cwd,\n  **then** a `## Restored Project Context` block appears in the session, containing the goal, up to N decisions, up to N gotchas, and last 5 progress entries.\n- **Given** the same project, **when** session starts, **then** importance-5 global memories are also injected.\n- **Given** total restored context exceeds 60 lines, **when** injected, **then** it is truncated to ~60 lines with a \"+N more — run /openltm:memory recall\" footer.\n\n### US-2 — Recall before deciding\n**As** Pat, **I want** `recall` to surface prior decisions on a topic, **so that** I don't contradict past work.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- **Given** a memory exists with text \"we use Bun, not npm\", **when** I call `recall(\"javascript package manager\")`, **then** that memory ranks in the top 3 results.\n- **Given** the same DB, **when** the FTS5 query returns < 3 results, **then** semantic fallback runs and merges results, deduplicated by id.\n- **Given** I pass `category: \"gotcha\"`, **when** I recall, **then** only gotchas are returned.\n- **Given** a project filter, **when** I recall, **then** only memories tagged with that project (or no project) are returned.\n\n### US-3 — Learn a decision in 1 keystroke\n**As** Sam, **I want** to capture a decision without leaving flow, **so that** I actually do it.\n","lineStart":145,"lineEnd":214,"totalLines":496,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","time":{"start":1780928806105,"end":1780928806135}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06533a27e20374c3016a26d125ff808191a44357598949f926"}},"id":"prt_ea7a0fcd6001o0rIuZIMx02EoG","sessionID":"ses_1586048c5ffertmP8HohyAZ8wd","messageID":"msg_ea7a0bde9001hGl1O24KkYMeLf"}}
